ome.datause:
Useful for identifying seasonal changes to the landscape.  Onset of snow and spring snowmelt for example. Note that date and time printed on the image are UTC. AKST is 9 hours behind UTC.&#xD;
&#xD;
Conversion of UTM (original coordinates: West/East 586024; North/South 7910257) to decimal degrees using the following tool http://www.rcn.montana.edu/Resources/Converter.aspx using the following selections - Datum NAD83, Standard UTM, Zone 4, Hemisphere N.
